going to have to be better at,

00:41:53.350 --> 00:41:54.650
you know, being dehydrated.

00:41:54.650 --> 00:41:55.950
Things like that.

00:41:55.950 --> 00:42:01.280
You do start to see evolution of
human beings in air with people

00:42:01.280 --> 00:42:05.500
who live on mountain tops
in Tibet and other places.

00:42:05.500 --> 00:42:10.200
They have a -- they have an
enhanced ability to breathe in --

00:42:10.200 --> 00:42:15.030
or I should say, they have a
more efficient breathing process,

00:42:15.030 --> 00:42:18.440
and they also have some
other biochemical changes

00:42:18.440 --> 00:42:22.090
that you can see directly in their
genes because they've just had

00:42:22.090 --> 00:42:25.170
to adapt to living
at higher elevations.

00:42:25.170 --> 00:42:27.530
So if we have to escape
to the mountains someday

00:42:27.530 --> 00:42:29.890
because it's too hot at sea level,

00:42:29.890 --> 00:42:31.540
it could be another
adaptation we have.

00:42:31.540 --> 00:42:34.520
So you probably will see
some changes in human beings

00:42:34.520 --> 00:42:38.580
over the course of the next
few millennia, unfortunately.

00:42:38.580 --> 00:42:40.470
But, again, I think that's it,
but thank you all for coming out.

00:42:40.470 --> 00:42:42.270
I appreciate it.

